  </figure>
  <p>There are some excellent CS Unplugged activities for understanding <url href="http://csunplugged.org/image-representation" visual="http://csunplugged.org/image-representation">image and color representation</url>.</p>
  <exercise label="Image_where_is_0_0">
    <statement>
      <p>11-9-1: Where is x = 0 y = 0 on an image?</p>
    </statement>
    <choices>
      <choice>
        <statement>
          <p>Middle of the image in width on the left side</p>
        </statement>
        <feedback>
          <p>y is 0 at the top left corner</p>
        </feedback>
      </choice>
      <choice>
        <statement>
          <p>Top right corner of the image</p>
        </statement>
        <feedback>
          <p>x is 0 at the left corner</p>
        </feedback>
      </choice>
      <choice>
        <statement>
          <p>Middle of the image in width and height</p>
        </statement>
        <feedback>
          <p>y is 0 at the top left corner and x is 0 on the left</p>
        </feedback>
      </choice>
      <choice correct="yes">
        <statement>
          <p>Top left corner of the image</p>
        </statement>
        <feedback>
          <p>Correct! x is 0 and y is 0 at the top left corner of the image</p>
        </feedback>
      </choice>
      <choice>
        <statement>
          <p>Bottom left corner of the image</p>
        </statement>
        <feedback>
          <p>y is 0 at the top and increases towards the bottom</p>
        </feedback>
      </choice>
    </choices>
  </exercise>
  <exercise label="Image_red_color">
    <statement>
      <p>11-9-2: What color would red = 255, green = 0, blue = 0 be?</p>
    </statement>
    <choices>
      <choice>
        <statement>
          <p>black</p>
        </statement>
        <feedback>
          <p>Black is an absence of light (all values are 0).</p>
        </feedback>
      </choice>
      <choice>
        <statement>
          <p>white</p>
        </statement>
        <feedback>
          <p>White is when all values are 255.</p>
        </feedback>
      </choice>
      <choice correct="yes">
        <statement>
          <p>red</p>
        </statement>
        <feedback>
          <p>If the green and blue are 0 and the red is 255 this will be red.</p>
        </feedback>
      </choice>
      <choice>
        <statement>
          <p>green</p>
        </statement>
        <feedback>
          <p>This would be true if the green was 255 and the other values were 0.</p>
        </feedback>
      </choice>
      <choice>
        <statement>
          <p>blue</p>
        </statement>
        <feedback>
          <p>This would be true if the blue was 255 and the other values were 0.</p>
        </feedback>
      </choice>
    </choices>
  </exercise>
</section>
